1
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:55,060
Hurry up. Let's go.

2
00:00:57,840 --> 00:00:58,400
Hurry up.

3
00:00:58,560 --> 00:00:59,160
Okay.

4
00:01:00,400 --> 00:01:01,060
I'm coming.

5
00:01:01,760 --> 00:01:03,760
You know what? We might actually have to chop wood.

6
00:01:03,760 --> 00:01:04,560
I told you so.

7
00:01:11,840 --> 00:01:12,640
Here it is.

8
00:01:25,120 --> 00:01:26,200
If you're tired,

9
00:01:26,880 --> 00:01:28,440
you can leave anytime.

10
00:01:30,080 --> 00:01:31,840
It's a new society now.

11
00:01:32,160 --> 00:01:34,620
Masters and apprentices can choose freely.

12
00:01:35,520 --> 00:01:36,600
In the past,

13
00:01:37,440 --> 00:01:39,800
would you dare speak to your master like that?

14
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:40,400
Master.

15
00:01:40,680 --> 00:01:42,800
There are so many people out there offering me money to fire kilns,

16
00:01:42,800 --> 00:01:43,660
but I didn't go.

17
00:01:45,360 --> 00:01:47,160
With your skills,

18
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:49,530
you dare go out and make a fool of yourself?

19
00:01:49,880 --> 00:01:51,479
Where am I lacking?

20
00:01:51,520 --> 00:01:52,479
Why won't you let me

21
00:01:52,479 --> 00:01:53,539
work at Weijiayao?

22
00:01:54,640 --> 00:01:55,280
Mr. Wei.

23
00:01:57,720 --> 00:01:58,360
Mr. Wei.

24
00:01:59,280 --> 00:01:59,810
Guan Lin,

25
00:02:00,640 --> 00:02:01,320
you're here.

26
00:02:01,320 --> 00:02:01,780
Mr. Wei.

27
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:04,440
Our class this afternoon

28
00:02:05,120 --> 00:02:06,850
will be held here at Weijiayao.

29
00:02:07,320 --> 00:02:08,050
Is that okay?

30
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:10,560
You led the restoration of this kiln.

31
00:02:10,600 --> 00:02:11,720
If you want to see it,

32
00:02:11,720 --> 00:02:12,960
how could I stop you?

33
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:16,000
Guan Lin.

34
00:02:16,320 --> 00:02:17,250
Take them there.

35
00:02:18,040 --> 00:02:19,480
Mr. Yue, this way.

36
00:02:19,840 --> 00:02:20,440
Come.

37
00:02:21,440 --> 00:02:22,440
You stubborn old man.

38
00:02:22,440 --> 00:02:24,440
Stop being so harsh with your words.

39
00:02:25,920 --> 00:02:27,400
What's Mr. Wei's background?

40
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:29,600
He doesn't even show respect to Mr. Yue.

41
00:02:30,040 --> 00:02:31,120
In Jingdezhen's traditional porcelain making,

42
00:02:31,120 --> 00:02:32,650
there are 72 steps in total.

43
00:02:32,680 --> 00:02:35,000
The most important one is firing the kiln.

44
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:36,320
There's a saying in the industry:

45
00:02:36,320 --> 00:02:38,200
"Success or failure depends on the kiln fire."

46
00:02:38,200 --> 00:02:39,160
Mr. Wei is the industry's

47
00:02:39,160 --> 00:02:40,760
renowned chief kiln master.

48
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:42,280
He is responsible for watching the fire.

49
00:02:42,280 --> 00:02:43,040
Mr. Yue.

50
00:02:43,200 --> 00:02:44,930
We looked at the photos before,

51
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:47,560
and the roof of the kiln had partially collapsed.

52
00:02:47,560 --> 00:02:48,960
How exactly did you repair it

53
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:50,240
so that it can reach the level

54
00:02:50,240 --> 00:02:51,770
of normal use like it is now?

55
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:53,880
The repair work by Mr. Yue's expert team

56
00:02:53,880 --> 00:02:57,640
is called kiln construction and repair in our professional jargon.

57
00:02:57,640 --> 00:02:59,440
To ensure that the repaired kiln

58
00:02:59,480 --> 00:03:01,040
can operate normally,

59
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:03,400
Mr. Yue first used the blueprints of Weijiayao

60
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:04,640
passed down from his master

61
00:03:04,640 --> 00:03:07,920
to precisely calculate the proportions

62
00:03:07,920 --> 00:03:09,560
and dimensions of the entire structure.

63
00:03:09,560 --> 00:03:10,920
Then he led the workers

64
00:03:10,920 --> 00:03:13,050
in piecing it together purely by hand.

65
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:14,040
Actually,

66
00:03:14,280 --> 00:03:16,480
in restoring a perfect arched kiln roof,

67
00:03:16,480 --> 00:03:17,740
every step is crucial.

68
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:19,120
Not only must each layer of kiln bricks

69
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:20,780
be evenly staggered inwards,

70
00:03:20,960 --> 00:03:21,600
but

71
00:03:21,960 --> 00:03:22,800
the bricks and mortar

72
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:24,600
must also be optimally matched.

73
00:03:25,040 --> 00:03:26,640
On the one hand, it's for firm adhesion

74
00:03:26,640 --> 00:03:27,720
to minimize gaps.

75
00:03:28,240 --> 00:03:29,240
On the other hand,

76
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:32,060
you must also use the tension created

77
00:03:32,360 --> 00:03:34,079
by the elliptical arrangement of the kiln bricks

78
00:03:34,079 --> 00:03:35,079
to ensure the roof

79
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:37,840
doesn't collapse while converging inwards.

80
00:03:37,840 --> 00:03:38,880
Wow, Xu Xiao.

81
00:03:39,160 --> 00:03:40,220
You even know this.

82
00:03:40,480 --> 00:03:42,360
Because when repairing the ancient kiln at the Imperial Kiln Factory,

83
00:03:42,360 --> 00:03:43,760
I actually moved bricks.

84
00:03:48,280 --> 00:03:48,880
Mr. Wei,

85
00:03:49,920 --> 00:03:51,380
can we discuss something?

86
00:03:52,040 --> 00:03:52,480
Go ahead.

87
00:03:52,480 --> 00:03:54,740
When you open the kiln in a couple of days,

88
00:03:55,079 --> 00:03:56,340
these students of mine

89
00:03:56,480 --> 00:03:58,880
will all come to observe and learn from you,

90
00:03:59,240 --> 00:04:00,300
and lend you a hand.

91
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:01,680
So many people?

92
00:04:02,280 --> 00:04:03,410
I can't handle them.

93
00:04:04,440 --> 00:04:05,560
Pick two.

94
00:04:07,560 --> 00:04:08,160
Then,

95
00:04:08,920 --> 00:04:09,400
you

96
00:04:10,360 --> 00:04:10,880
and you.

97
00:04:11,080 --> 00:04:11,680
You two,

98
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:13,460
have them come over on Sunday.

99
00:04:14,440 --> 00:04:16,160
Why us two?

100
00:04:16,360 --> 00:04:18,399
There's no why.

101
00:04:19,920 --> 00:04:21,850
Can't I just randomly pick you two?

102
00:04:21,880 --> 00:04:23,480
In a picturesque place like this,

103
00:04:23,480 --> 00:04:24,480
not falling in love

104
00:04:24,480 --> 00:04:26,320
would be a waste of the beautiful scenery.

105
00:04:26,320 --> 00:04:27,080
Yue.

106
00:04:27,360 --> 00:04:29,160
You have it easy leading a class.

107
00:04:29,400 --> 00:04:30,200
What's wrong?

108
00:04:30,400 --> 00:04:32,659
With so many students, you have choices.

109
00:04:33,320 --> 00:04:34,240
Unlike me,

110
00:04:35,280 --> 00:04:36,240
I only have one.

111
00:04:37,280 --> 00:04:37,880
Mr. Wei,

112
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:39,000
you are

113
00:04:39,440 --> 00:04:40,770
more dedicated than me.

114
00:04:41,520 --> 00:04:42,600
We all know that.

115
00:04:43,280 --> 00:04:44,480
Come on. Let's start.

116
00:04:54,360 --> 00:04:54,960
Thank you.

117
00:04:56,760 --> 00:04:59,020
Your explanation today was really good.

118
00:04:59,360 --> 00:05:00,760
Next time you come to the imperial kiln,

119
00:05:00,760 --> 00:05:02,220
just contact me directly.

120
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:13,050
Let's go sit over there.

121
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:13,920
Okay.

122
00:05:42,440 --> 00:05:43,880
The weather is really nice today.

123
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:44,200
Yes.

124
00:05:44,440 --> 00:05:46,680
Because Jingdezhen has a subtropical monsoon climate,

125
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:47,400
and is surrounded by mountains,

126
00:05:47,400 --> 00:05:49,120
it has plenty of sunlight and distinct seasons.

127
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:51,380
The temperature is mild and humid, so...

128
00:05:53,159 --> 00:05:55,620
Sorry, I seem to be explaining things again.

129
00:06:06,240 --> 00:06:08,080
Are you busy at school recently?

130
00:06:09,080 --> 00:06:09,960
It's okay.

131
00:06:10,320 --> 00:06:11,320
Recently, Mr. Liang

132
00:06:11,320 --> 00:06:13,000
taught us the craft of Tang Tri-colored Glazed Pottery.

133
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:14,880
Mr. Yue taught us kintsugi.

134
00:06:14,880 --> 00:06:16,240
Mr. Lin also taught us about

135
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:17,570
many types of ceramics.

136
00:06:17,720 --> 00:06:18,200
I

137
00:06:18,560 --> 00:06:19,960
have learned quite a lot.

138
00:06:22,640 --> 00:06:23,880
That is quite a lot.

139
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:37,240
Yuexin.

140
00:06:39,920 --> 00:06:41,520
I have something to tell you.

141
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:46,700
I've kept these words in my heart for a long time.

142
00:06:47,760 --> 00:06:49,490
I've always wanted to tell you.

143
00:06:52,640 --> 00:06:53,320
I like you.

144
00:06:58,560 --> 00:06:59,080
Yuexin,

145
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:01,740
will you go out with me?

146
00:07:32,960 --> 00:07:34,600
Sorry, I have something to do.

147
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:35,860
I have to go back first.

148
00:07:36,640 --> 00:07:37,760
I...

149
00:07:38,200 --> 00:07:39,000
I'll walk you.

150
00:07:39,320 --> 00:07:40,000
No, no need.

151
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:41,120
I can go by myself.

152
00:08:05,040 --> 00:08:05,640
Xiaocen.

153
00:08:05,640 --> 00:08:06,240
Hello.

154
00:08:06,240 --> 00:08:06,840
Xiaocen.

155
00:08:06,840 --> 00:08:07,680
Xiaocen.

156
00:08:08,280 --> 00:08:09,610
What are you doing here?

157
00:08:09,760 --> 00:08:11,420
I... I'm just zoning out here.

158
00:08:11,840 --> 00:08:13,600
We found an interesting restaurant for tonight.

159
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:14,760
Wang Lin went ahead to line up.

160
00:08:14,760 --> 00:08:16,120
Do you want to come with us?

161
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:18,380
What if Xiaocen has other plans tonight?

162
00:08:18,560 --> 00:08:20,480
She's just standing here. What could she possibly have to do?

163
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:20,840
Yeah.

164
00:08:20,840 --> 00:08:21,440
Didn't you say

165
00:08:21,440 --> 00:08:23,240
we should invite her to everything?

166
00:08:23,240 --> 00:08:23,970
Come with us.

167
00:08:24,360 --> 00:08:25,280
Let's go.

168
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:27,660
So many people.

169
00:08:28,520 --> 00:08:28,980
Xu Xiao.

170
00:08:30,240 --> 00:08:31,200
We're grabbing dinner tonight.

171
00:08:31,200 --> 00:08:32,260
Wanna come with us?

172
00:08:33,679 --> 00:08:35,539
You guys are going out for dinner?

173
00:08:36,679 --> 00:08:37,120
Yeah.

174
00:08:39,960 --> 00:08:41,490
I have other plans tonight.

175
00:08:41,520 --> 00:08:42,039
I won't be joining you.

176
00:08:42,039 --> 00:08:42,760
What plans?

177
00:08:43,679 --> 00:08:44,159
I'm off.

178
00:08:46,920 --> 00:08:47,560
Xu Xiao.

179
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:54,600
How about going tonight?

180
00:08:54,920 --> 00:08:56,580
You have nothing to do anyway.

181
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:59,300
How do you know if he has nothing to do?

182
00:08:59,560 --> 00:09:00,820
Because we originally

183
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:02,840
planned to eat together.

184
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:05,730
What does that mean?

185
00:09:13,720 --> 00:09:14,240
Oh my god.

186
00:09:14,240 --> 00:09:15,880
I told you there was something going on between them.

187
00:09:15,880 --> 00:09:17,040
I told you so.

188
00:09:17,040 --> 00:09:17,760
Wait, since when?

189
00:09:17,760 --> 00:09:19,360
Xiaocen just made it public like that?

190
00:09:19,360 --> 00:09:20,960
Aren't these my lovely students?

191
00:09:20,960 --> 00:09:22,600
What are you doing?

192
00:09:29,640 --> 00:09:31,600
Alright, see you in class tomorrow.

193
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:32,730
Goodbye, Mr. Liang.

194
00:09:33,360 --> 00:09:35,440
This is youth. Youth.

195
00:09:35,760 --> 00:09:36,480
Hurry up and tell us,

196
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:37,120
you two.

197
00:09:37,120 --> 00:09:38,320
When did this happen?

198
00:09:38,800 --> 00:09:40,040
When did this happen? Tell us.

199
00:09:40,040 --> 00:09:41,520
Details, details, details!

200
00:09:41,520 --> 00:09:42,080
Tell us, tell us, tell us!

201
00:09:42,080 --> 00:09:43,340
I'll tell you tonight.

202
00:10:02,880 --> 00:10:04,340
Why is there no water here?

203
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:05,200
Yuexin.

204
00:10:25,280 --> 00:10:26,400
You two chat first.

205
00:10:26,400 --> 00:10:28,040
I'll go buy some water.

206
00:10:45,480 --> 00:10:48,340
Why didn't you tell me you came to the Imperial Kiln?

207
00:10:48,880 --> 00:10:50,280
Yan Xue dragged me here.

208
00:10:51,080 --> 00:10:52,920
I was afraid of disturbing your work.

209
00:10:52,920 --> 00:10:53,800
So I...

210
00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:55,650
You weren't looking for me.

211
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:02,090
About last time,

212
00:11:02,800 --> 00:11:03,400
I'm sorry.

213
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:04,840
I scared you.

214
00:11:06,640 --> 00:11:06,960
No.

215
00:11:07,480 --> 00:11:08,000
I...

216
00:11:09,040 --> 00:11:09,640
If

217
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:11,860
you haven't made up your mind,

218
00:11:12,720 --> 00:11:14,380
I can prove it with my actions.

219
00:11:18,960 --> 00:11:20,320
If you don't like me,

220
00:11:21,240 --> 00:11:22,500
just tell me directly.

221
00:11:22,920 --> 00:11:23,640
It's okay.

222
00:11:23,880 --> 00:11:24,280
I...

223
00:11:24,480 --> 00:11:26,360
I don't want you to feel too much pressure.

224
00:11:26,360 --> 00:11:26,720
I...

225
00:11:35,840 --> 00:11:37,800
It's actually not like that.

226
00:11:40,440 --> 00:11:41,920
Since we met,

227
00:11:42,320 --> 00:11:45,120
you've always been the one taking the initiative.

228
00:11:45,920 --> 00:11:47,560
I know you care about me a lot.

229
00:11:49,320 --> 00:11:50,800
When I was in a bad mood,

230
00:11:50,920 --> 00:11:52,780
you were the one who cheered me up.

231
00:11:52,840 --> 00:11:54,770
Whenever I ran into difficulties,

232
00:11:54,800 --> 00:11:57,130
you always actively helped me solve them.

233
00:11:59,040 --> 00:12:02,240
Actually, I know how you feel.

234
00:12:03,640 --> 00:12:04,900
Then what do you think?

235
00:12:07,040 --> 00:12:07,840
I'm scared.

236
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:08,920
Scared?

237
00:12:12,560 --> 00:12:13,480
I think

238
00:12:13,680 --> 00:12:15,800
you seem very good at talking to girls

239
00:12:17,440 --> 00:12:19,440
and you're a few years older than me.

240
00:12:20,040 --> 00:12:21,240
So I thought

241
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:23,440
you could easily fall for someone else.

242
00:12:23,960 --> 00:12:24,400
I...

243
00:12:25,160 --> 00:12:25,840
Actually,

244
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:27,840
um, Yan Xue is still waiting for me.

245
00:12:27,840 --> 00:12:28,700
I'll get going.

246
00:12:44,920 --> 00:12:45,600
Cencen.

247
00:12:46,640 --> 00:12:48,000
Come out and have some steamed egg.

248
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:49,080
I saw you didn't eat much for dinner.

249
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:50,520
Is your stomach hurting again?

250
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:52,080
No, I'm reviewing.

251
00:12:53,280 --> 00:12:53,880
It's fine.

252
00:13:00,640 --> 00:13:01,440
Cencen.

253
00:13:03,120 --> 00:13:05,250
I brought you a hot water bottle. Here.

254
00:13:05,600 --> 00:13:06,060
Hold it.

255
00:13:06,640 --> 00:13:08,480
Mom, I don't want it. It's too hot.

256
00:13:08,480 --> 00:13:09,360
What do you mean too hot?

257
00:13:09,360 --> 00:13:10,560
The heat will make you feel better.

258
00:13:10,560 --> 00:13:11,600
Don't I know you?

259
00:13:11,720 --> 00:13:12,560
Okay.

260
00:13:13,680 --> 00:13:15,140
Alright, I'm heading out.

261
00:13:17,520 --> 00:13:18,440
Cencen.

262
00:13:19,120 --> 00:13:20,600
Here, some tomatoes.

263
00:13:20,680 --> 00:13:21,880
Tomatoes.

264
00:13:21,920 --> 00:13:23,120
I'll leave them here.

265
00:13:23,320 --> 00:13:23,800
This way,

266
00:13:23,800 --> 00:13:24,860
it's easier to eat.

267
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:25,920
Okay.

268
00:13:25,960 --> 00:13:28,200
Sister, just let Xiaocen be by herself.

269
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:29,720
She is studying.

270
00:13:29,920 --> 00:13:31,320
I know.

271
00:13:31,960 --> 00:13:33,120
It's the weekend,

272
00:13:33,120 --> 00:13:35,160
why do they assign you so many things?

273
00:13:35,160 --> 00:13:36,320
Why do we even have weekends then?

274
00:13:36,320 --> 00:13:37,720
It means there is time to study,

275
00:13:37,720 --> 00:13:38,840
and time to rest.

276
00:13:38,840 --> 00:13:39,680
If you don't rest well,

277
00:13:39,680 --> 00:13:40,940
how can you study well?

278
00:13:41,880 --> 00:13:42,640
If it doesn't work out,

279
00:13:42,640 --> 00:13:44,760
I'll ask your class teacher for a leave.

280
00:13:44,760 --> 00:13:45,200
Mom,

281
00:13:45,360 --> 00:13:46,480
this is a rare opportunity.

282
00:13:46,480 --> 00:13:47,560
Just let me go.

283
00:13:47,840 --> 00:13:48,320
Come on, Mom.

284
00:13:48,320 --> 00:13:49,120
But aren't you feeling unwell?

285
00:13:49,120 --> 00:13:49,800
Mom, go out.

286
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:51,280
I will definitely eat the tomatoes.

287
00:13:51,280 --> 00:13:52,320
Don't push me.

288
00:13:52,520 --> 00:13:53,200
You go out first.

289
00:13:53,200 --> 00:13:54,160
You sit.

290
00:13:54,640 --> 00:13:55,280
Okay.

291
00:13:55,560 --> 00:13:56,240
You sit.

292
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:00,660
Put the hot water bottle back.

293
00:14:01,240 --> 00:14:02,240
Got it.

294
00:14:04,760 --> 00:14:05,760
Eat the tomatoes.

295
00:14:07,280 --> 00:14:08,320
Rest early.

296
00:14:22,200 --> 00:14:22,760
How is it?

297
00:14:23,160 --> 00:14:24,290
How are you feeling?

298
00:14:24,720 --> 00:14:25,680
What do you mean?

299
00:14:25,680 --> 00:14:26,960
Tell me. Don't dawdle.

300
00:14:27,720 --> 00:14:28,720
It's just that...

301
00:14:28,800 --> 00:14:29,330
Xiaocen,

302
00:14:29,600 --> 00:14:30,800
you've been spending so much time

303
00:14:30,800 --> 00:14:32,280
alone with Xu Xiao in Weijiayao lately.

304
00:14:32,280 --> 00:14:33,200
How far have you two progressed?

305
00:14:33,200 --> 00:14:34,480
Yeah, how far have you progressed?

306
00:14:34,480 --> 00:14:35,960
Not very far.

307
00:14:37,120 --> 00:14:38,120
And...

308
00:14:39,560 --> 00:14:40,890
What's wrong, Xiaocen?

309
00:14:41,600 --> 00:14:43,920
We even had a little argument.

310
00:14:44,720 --> 00:14:45,920
What's going on here?

311
00:14:48,120 --> 00:14:50,780
So what's the progress between you and Xiaocen?

312
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:53,200
It's a long story.

313
00:14:56,880 --> 00:14:59,000
That day, right as we arrived at Master Wei's door,

314
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:01,460
we heard the sound of porcelain shattering.

315
00:15:01,920 --> 00:15:02,450
Let's go.

316
00:15:05,040 --> 00:15:05,700
Master Wei.

317
00:15:07,640 --> 00:15:08,170
Guan Lin.

318
00:15:08,280 --> 00:15:08,810
Guan Lin.

319
00:15:10,440 --> 00:15:11,440
I'll go after him.

320
00:15:11,480 --> 00:15:13,140
Ask him what really happened.

321
00:15:25,880 --> 00:15:26,480
Guan Lin,

322
00:15:27,440 --> 00:15:28,300
what happened?

323
00:15:29,240 --> 00:15:30,120
Nothing.

324
00:15:30,880 --> 00:15:31,920
What could happen to me?

325
00:15:31,920 --> 00:15:33,200
So the Spring brings good fortune and harmony fat belly vase

326
00:15:33,200 --> 00:15:34,400
that Mr. Wei smashed just now,

327
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:35,680
Yes, I made it.

328
00:15:38,440 --> 00:15:40,440
I don't know much about high-temperature color glaze,

329
00:15:40,440 --> 00:15:41,720
but I know that the Spring brings good fortune and harmony fat belly vase

330
00:15:41,720 --> 00:15:43,180
is extremely hard to make.

331
00:15:43,560 --> 00:15:45,120
And judging by the glaze color,

332
00:15:45,120 --> 00:15:46,250
it's a masterpiece.

333
00:15:46,800 --> 00:15:47,840
Why did Mr. Wei...

334
00:15:50,280 --> 00:15:52,410
He just doesn't want to acknowledge me

335
00:15:52,600 --> 00:15:54,860
or let me touch the Wei family's old kiln.

336
00:15:56,560 --> 00:15:57,360
Xu Xiao,

337
00:15:57,760 --> 00:15:59,220
I developed the technique

338
00:15:59,360 --> 00:16:01,440
and made that fat belly vase myself.

339
00:16:01,600 --> 00:16:02,680
Everyone in the village said it was good,

340
00:16:02,680 --> 00:16:03,640
but he said it wasn't

341
00:16:03,640 --> 00:16:05,160
and smashed it right away.

342
00:16:07,200 --> 00:16:08,530
What did the master say?

343
00:16:12,360 --> 00:16:12,880
Yes,

344
00:16:13,720 --> 00:16:14,800
I smashed it.

345
00:16:16,440 --> 00:16:16,960
Mr. Wei,

346
00:16:16,960 --> 00:16:19,160
why did you smash Guan Lin's porcelain?

347
00:16:19,640 --> 00:16:21,040
It turned out like that.

348
00:16:21,800 --> 00:16:23,240
Shouldn't I smash it?

349
00:16:25,440 --> 00:16:26,160
Mr. Wei,

350
00:16:27,360 --> 00:16:29,600
no matter how Guan Lin did,

351
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:33,240
aren't you being too harsh on him?

352
00:16:34,240 --> 00:16:35,160
Xiaocen,

353
00:16:35,840 --> 00:16:36,960
do you know

354
00:16:37,080 --> 00:16:40,080
how many people don't value the art of kiln firing?

355
00:16:40,280 --> 00:16:42,120
It's too dirty and tiring.

356
00:16:42,640 --> 00:16:45,440
Plus, modern kilns have their own firing methods.

357
00:16:45,440 --> 00:16:46,520
What they value

358
00:16:46,800 --> 00:16:47,960
is heat utilization

359
00:16:48,560 --> 00:16:50,480
and temperature measurement equipment.

360
00:16:50,480 --> 00:16:52,400
No one values kiln firing.

361
00:16:52,920 --> 00:16:54,680
They say it's only a matter of time

362
00:16:54,680 --> 00:16:56,160
before this job is eliminated.

363
00:16:56,160 --> 00:16:57,480
I don't think so.

364
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:00,440
On the contrary,

365
00:17:01,040 --> 00:17:01,960
kiln firing

366
00:17:02,240 --> 00:17:03,640
is the most important part

367
00:17:03,640 --> 00:17:07,720
of the traditional Chai Kiln firing process.

368
00:17:08,560 --> 00:17:10,599
I can't let such a heavy responsibility

369
00:17:10,599 --> 00:17:12,400
end with my apprentice.

370
00:17:14,520 --> 00:17:15,980
So if he makes it like that,

371
00:17:16,160 --> 00:17:17,319
it must be smashed.

372
00:17:21,160 --> 00:17:21,800
Xu Xiao,

373
00:17:22,560 --> 00:17:23,280
do you know?

374
00:17:23,720 --> 00:17:24,599
From the first day

375
00:17:24,599 --> 00:17:26,000
I became his apprentice,

376
00:17:26,599 --> 00:17:28,400
he showed me his medical report.

377
00:17:29,560 --> 00:17:30,490
Stomach cancer.

378
00:17:31,480 --> 00:17:32,160
What?

379
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:34,400
The master has cancer,

380
00:17:34,720 --> 00:17:37,250
why is the apprentice still arguing with him?

381
00:17:37,320 --> 00:17:38,780
Actually, I think Guan Lin

382
00:17:39,120 --> 00:17:40,250
has his own reasons.

383
00:17:42,840 --> 00:17:44,560
But Mr. Wei looks so healthy.

384
00:17:45,080 --> 00:17:46,520
I thought he was perfectly fine.

385
00:17:46,520 --> 00:17:47,480
You're right.

386
00:17:47,720 --> 00:17:48,720
He is fine.

387
00:17:49,880 --> 00:17:51,040
The doctor said at the time

388
00:17:51,040 --> 00:17:52,440
he only had three months left.

389
00:17:52,440 --> 00:17:53,320
I pitied him,

390
00:17:53,480 --> 00:17:54,840
so I stayed to take care of him.

391
00:17:54,840 --> 00:17:56,680
I really don't want anything in return.

392
00:17:56,680 --> 00:17:57,200
I just

393
00:17:57,480 --> 00:17:59,200
respect a senior like him from the bottom of my heart.

394
00:17:59,200 --> 00:17:59,840
Yes.

395
00:17:59,840 --> 00:18:02,160
There aren't many master kiln operators like Mr. Wei in Jingdezhen.

396
00:18:02,160 --> 00:18:03,020
I can count them

397
00:18:03,400 --> 00:18:04,560
on one hand.

398
00:18:04,880 --> 00:18:05,280
Right.

399
00:18:06,120 --> 00:18:07,000
But Xu Xiao,

400
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:08,920
Three months.

401
00:18:10,040 --> 00:18:11,800
That was five years ago.

402
00:18:12,640 --> 00:18:13,520
In these five years,

403
00:18:13,520 --> 00:18:16,000
I fed him, made his bed, and cleaned up after him.

404
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:16,930
For three years,

405
00:18:17,080 --> 00:18:18,480
I barely even went home.

406
00:18:18,960 --> 00:18:21,560
Now he eats well and sleeps soundly.

407
00:18:21,880 --> 00:18:23,840
He's getting stronger every day.

408
00:18:24,080 --> 00:18:25,810
I feel like he might outlive me.

409
00:18:26,240 --> 00:18:26,600
Yes.

410
00:18:27,080 --> 00:18:28,800
Guan Lin, it's been hard on you.

411
00:18:28,800 --> 00:18:29,680
You can all see

412
00:18:30,480 --> 00:18:31,360
how hard he is to please.

413
00:18:31,360 --> 00:18:32,420
He has a huge temper

414
00:18:32,480 --> 00:18:33,680
and is picky about his food.

415
00:18:33,680 --> 00:18:34,320
As for vegetables,

416
00:18:34,320 --> 00:18:35,480
he insists on growing them himself.

417
00:18:35,480 --> 00:18:37,610
Why doesn't he raise pigs himself too?

418
00:18:38,320 --> 00:18:39,520
He refuses to go to the hospital,

419
00:18:39,520 --> 00:18:40,480
refuses to get injections,

420
00:18:40,480 --> 00:18:41,520
and refuses to take medicine.

421
00:18:41,520 --> 00:18:42,680
Every time we go to the hospital,

422
00:18:42,680 --> 00:18:44,360
it's like coaxing a child.

423
00:18:44,480 --> 00:18:46,160
If I'm not paying attention, he's off smoking

424
00:18:46,160 --> 00:18:46,960
or drinking.

425
00:18:47,640 --> 00:18:49,300
Do you know what he's taught me

426
00:18:49,720 --> 00:18:50,920
in these three years?

427
00:18:51,320 --> 00:18:52,200
Look at me.

428
00:18:54,840 --> 00:18:55,440
Spitting.

429
00:18:55,680 --> 00:18:56,320
Just this.

430
00:18:57,160 --> 00:18:59,280
He says that at the critical moment,

431
00:18:59,280 --> 00:19:00,800
you can estimate the temperature

432
00:19:00,800 --> 00:19:01,960
based on how the spit burns

433
00:19:01,960 --> 00:19:03,040
when you spit into the kiln.

434
00:19:03,040 --> 00:19:03,900
I believed him.

435
00:19:04,200 --> 00:19:05,200
But just for this,

436
00:19:06,120 --> 00:19:07,120
it shouldn't take three years, right?

437
00:19:07,120 --> 00:19:07,640
Yes.

438
00:19:09,240 --> 00:19:11,720
Speaking of spitting,

439
00:19:12,880 --> 00:19:15,240
it's about observing how the spit burns

440
00:19:15,560 --> 00:19:17,320
to help judge the temperature.

441
00:19:18,480 --> 00:19:20,200
It sounds simple,

442
00:19:20,480 --> 00:19:22,080
but there are very few people

443
00:19:22,080 --> 00:19:23,610
who can actually master it.

444
00:19:24,920 --> 00:19:26,360
Besides, nowadays,

445
00:19:26,880 --> 00:19:28,480
there's temperature-measuring equipment.

446
00:19:28,480 --> 00:19:30,800
Electric kilns make firing even easier.

447
00:19:31,840 --> 00:19:32,320
Then,

448
00:19:32,720 --> 00:19:36,360
why is it that the things fired in kilns

449
00:19:36,360 --> 00:19:38,240
from any other country in the world

450
00:19:38,240 --> 00:19:40,120
cannot be compared with the things

451
00:19:40,120 --> 00:19:41,520
fired in our traditional

452
00:19:41,520 --> 00:19:43,440
Chinese kilns?

453
00:19:44,480 --> 00:19:45,400
That is because

454
00:19:45,920 --> 00:19:47,050
the art of porcelain

455
00:19:47,440 --> 00:19:49,520
is the art of fire.

456
00:19:52,240 --> 00:19:54,120
In all my years as an apprentice,

457
00:19:54,440 --> 00:19:57,400
I've seen so many firing failures.

458
00:19:58,880 --> 00:20:00,200
That brat Guan Lin,

459
00:20:00,520 --> 00:20:02,320
he's seen too few.

460
00:20:05,240 --> 00:20:06,000
Mr. Wei.

461
00:20:06,680 --> 00:20:08,740
Experience isn't gained overnight.

462
00:20:09,400 --> 00:20:11,930
You have to let Guan Lin experience it slowly.

463
00:20:13,920 --> 00:20:15,920
I'm afraid there's no time.

464
00:20:19,840 --> 00:20:22,440
So the master and apprentice just fell out like that.

465
00:20:22,440 --> 00:20:24,440
Then what did you and Xu Xiao do next?

466
00:20:39,560 --> 00:20:40,160
Mr. Wei,

467
00:20:41,600 --> 00:20:42,520
these sherds,

468
00:20:43,360 --> 00:20:44,490
can I take them back?

469
00:20:47,160 --> 00:20:48,360
Do whatever you want.

470
00:21:02,120 --> 00:21:02,800
Xu Xiao,

471
00:21:03,360 --> 00:21:05,690
how did you persuade Guan Lin to come back?

472
00:21:07,480 --> 00:21:09,540
Guan Lin didn't really want to leave.

473
00:21:10,200 --> 00:21:11,600
He just felt too wronged.

474
00:21:13,120 --> 00:21:14,720
He did so much for his master,

475
00:21:14,880 --> 00:21:16,480
but still couldn't get recognized.

476
00:21:16,480 --> 00:21:18,240
Actually, I don't understand either.

477
00:21:18,240 --> 00:21:19,570
Mr. Wei is in poor health

478
00:21:19,840 --> 00:21:21,920
and has only Guan Lin as his apprentice.

479
00:21:21,920 --> 00:21:23,520
Why can't he let him take over as soon as possible?

480
00:21:23,520 --> 00:21:24,760
What Mr. Wei wants to pass on

481
00:21:24,760 --> 00:21:26,090
is his lifelong skills,

482
00:21:26,680 --> 00:21:28,640
so he has to be stricter with his evaluation.

483
00:21:28,640 --> 00:21:30,560
But he shouldn't dismiss Guan Lin.

484
00:21:30,560 --> 00:21:32,960
Everyone has their own independent thoughts.

485
00:21:32,960 --> 00:21:35,360
A master shouldn't impart knowledge on the one hand,

486
00:21:35,360 --> 00:21:36,290
and on the other,

487
00:21:36,520 --> 00:21:38,280
tightly control his apprentice.

488
00:21:38,280 --> 00:21:40,410
I think Mr. Wei means well for Guan Lin.

489
00:21:41,200 --> 00:21:43,440
Look, he only has Guan Lin as his apprentice.

490
00:21:43,440 --> 00:21:44,370
Just like my mom.

491
00:21:45,560 --> 00:21:47,420
I know she sacrificed a lot for me.

492
00:21:47,840 --> 00:21:50,920
Even though there are some things I just can't understand.

493
00:21:50,920 --> 00:21:52,650
But you are different from her.

494
00:21:52,720 --> 00:21:53,640
Maybe you are just forcing yourself

495
00:21:53,640 --> 00:21:54,920
to accept it.

496
00:22:05,800 --> 00:22:07,060
No, I didn't mean that.

497
00:22:22,320 --> 00:22:24,450
So did you and Xu Xiao make up in the end?

498
00:22:25,400 --> 00:22:26,520
Actually, I

499
00:22:27,040 --> 00:22:29,300
don't even know if it counts as making up.

500
00:22:30,440 --> 00:22:33,040
And I don't even know if that counted as a fight.

501
00:22:33,760 --> 00:22:34,760
Then go coax her.

502
00:22:37,320 --> 00:22:38,980
I don't know how to coax girls.

503
00:22:39,720 --> 00:22:40,720
Coaxing girls,

504
00:22:40,840 --> 00:22:41,880
I'm very good at it.

505
00:22:41,880 --> 00:22:43,000
Why didn't you ask me?

506
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:43,960
I can teach you.

507
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:45,600
Thank you.

508
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:47,160
You're welcome.

509
00:22:49,960 --> 00:22:51,020
Where is Zhuoting?

510
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:52,880
Zhuoting?

511
00:22:54,400 --> 00:22:56,000
He went on a date with Xiaoyi.

512
00:22:57,400 --> 00:22:58,040
Sorry.

513
00:22:58,880 --> 00:22:59,480
It's fine.

514
00:22:59,920 --> 00:23:00,760
I've moved on.

515
00:24:23,240 --> 00:24:23,720
Hello.

516
00:24:24,040 --> 00:24:24,480
Sir.

517
00:24:25,760 --> 00:24:27,160
I want to look at the cups.

518
00:24:27,440 --> 00:24:28,960
Which surname are you looking for?

519
00:24:28,960 --> 00:24:29,960
Do you have Zhang?

520
00:24:30,400 --> 00:24:31,000
Yes, we do.

521
00:25:36,640 --> 00:25:37,360
I'm sorry.

522
00:25:38,560 --> 00:25:39,960
Earlier on the mountain,

523
00:25:40,880 --> 00:25:42,140
I said the wrong thing.

524
00:25:45,800 --> 00:25:47,720
You were the one who wouldn't talk to me.

525
00:25:47,720 --> 00:25:48,980
I thought you were mad,

526
00:25:49,840 --> 00:25:50,900
so I didn't dare to.

527
00:25:52,560 --> 00:25:54,280
Actually, I wasn't mad.

528
00:25:57,040 --> 00:25:58,840
You just hit the nail on the head,

529
00:25:58,840 --> 00:25:59,770
so I got anxious.

530
00:26:00,760 --> 00:26:02,690
I really do always listen to my mom.

531
00:26:03,840 --> 00:26:05,240
I didn't mean it that way.

532
00:26:06,640 --> 00:26:08,900
Actually, just like Mr. Wei and Guan Lin,

533
00:26:09,400 --> 00:26:10,920
they don't have any fundamental conflicts.

534
00:26:10,920 --> 00:26:12,280
They just didn't put themselves

535
00:26:12,280 --> 00:26:13,480
in the other's shoes.

536
00:26:14,800 --> 00:26:16,660
I didn't consider your feelings.

537
00:26:21,280 --> 00:26:22,540
I accept your apology.

538
00:26:24,200 --> 00:26:24,800
I'm sorry.

539
00:26:26,600 --> 00:26:27,320
Can you forgive me?
